WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.960
We brought a trailer in for our micro entrepreneur offices

00:00:03.960 --> 00:00:05.680
that is in front of our garden.

00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:08.080
And so we have our garden and multiple garden beds

00:00:08.080 --> 00:00:09.860
out on the patio.

00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:12.240
We use the space where our apprentices eat their breakfast

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:14.600
and lunch for pop-up restaurants.

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:19.160
It's truly just, it's been a wonderful home for us,

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:22.320
but we are at the point that we have had to step back.

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:25.220
One of the reasons we no longer do hunger relief meals

00:00:25.220 --> 00:00:28.020
on the regular is because our kitchen is only

00:00:28.060 --> 00:00:30.620
so many square feet and we have to train our apprentices.

00:00:30.620 --> 00:00:32.540
That's always the heart of our program.

00:00:32.540 --> 00:00:35.380
And we are the meal contract

00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:36.920
for the juvenile detention facilities.

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:41.920
And we're doing, you know, over three meals a day

00:00:41.980 --> 00:00:46.980
for 300 kids, three snacks a day, 365 days a year.

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:49.760
And so some of that prep happens in our kitchen

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:52.660
and between the training and the micro entrepreneurs

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:55.700
and that meal contract, that kitchen is running

00:00:55.700 --> 00:00:57.340
22 hours a day.
